This is how to next_smallest of lst:
   Remember that n is lst's length
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is []
   End when
   Remember that smallest is item 0 in lst
   Remember that i is 1
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that x is item i in lst
      When x is less than smallest, then:
         Remember that smallest is x
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that found is 0
   Remember that answer is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that x is item i in lst
      When x is more than smallest, then:
         When found is 0, then:
            Remember that answer is [x]
            Remember that found is 1
         But, if not:
            When x is less than item 0 in answer, then:
               Remember that answer is [x]
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is answer
